OL,5,Ccartridges
OL,7,FProsecutors said she breached a high
OL,8,Fdegree of trust, and described the
OL,9,Foffending as 'sophisticated' as she
OL,10,Fwas able to sell the cartridges on for
OL,11,Fher own 'criminal enterprise'.
OL,13,FIn mitigation, Eleanor Brambell said
OL,14,Fher client was facing a lengthy term
OL,15,Fin prison, though asked the court for
OL,16,Fleniency.
OL,18,FShe said Timmins was the sole carer of
OL,19,Fher seven-year-old son, and also cared
OL,20,Ffor her mum, who would regularly get
OL,21,Fplaced into 'medically induced comas'.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
